sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (edge TLS)
    participant UI as Streamlit UI<br/>8501/TCP HTTP
    participant API as Backend API<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Ollama as Ollama LLM<br/>11434/TCP HTTP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MC as Model Catalog<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User, K8s: Flow 1: Conversational Recommendation Workflow

    User->>Route: HTTPS/443 (TLS edge)
    Route->>UI: HTTP/8501
    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/extract<br/>HTTP/8000 (Natural language requirements)
    API->>Ollama: POST /api/generate<br/>HTTP/11434 (granite3.3:2b)
    Ollama-->>API: Extracted intent (model, use_case, priorities)
    API-->>UI: Intent specification

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/ranked-recommend-from-spec<br/>HTTP/8000
    API->>PG: Query exported_summaries<br/>PostgreSQL/5432 (Password auth)
    PG-->>API: Benchmark results
    API->>HF: GET model config<br/>HTTPS/443 (HF_TOKEN optional)
    HF-->>API: Model architecture metadata
    Note over API: Score on 4 criteria:<br/>accuracy, price, latency, complexity<br/>Generate 5 ranked lists
    API-->>UI: Ranked recommendations (5 lists)

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/deploy<br/>HTTP/8000 (Selected config)
    Note over API: Jinja2 renders:<br/>InferenceService + HPA + ServiceMonitor
    API-->>UI: Generated YAML manifests

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/deploy-to-cluster<br/>HTTP/8000
    API->>K8s: kubectl apply<br/>HTTPS/6443 (SA Token)
    K8s-->>API: Deployment status
    API-->>UI: Deployment confirmation
    UI-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User, K8s: Flow 2: Capacity Planning

    User->>Route: HTTPS/443
    Route->>UI: HTTP/8501
    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/model-info<br/>HTTP/8000
    API->>HF: GET model config<br/>HTTPS/443
    HF-->>API: Model params, architecture
    API-->>UI: Model metadata

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/calculate<br/>HTTP/8000
    Note over API: Calculate GPU memory:<br/>weights + KV cache + activation
    API-->>UI: Memory requirements per GPU type

    Note over API, MC: Flow 3: Model Catalog Sync (Optional RHOAI)

    Note over API: Background thread (periodic)
    API->>MC: GET benchmarks<br/>HTTPS/8443 (Bearer Token, Service CA TLS)
    MC-->>API: Benchmark data
    API->>PG: UPSERT benchmarks<br/>PostgreSQL/5432
